What is the work function of the metal if the light of wavelength 4000$$\mathop A\limits^ \circ  $$ generates photoelectrons of velocity 6 $$ \times $$ 10<sup>5</sup>  ms<sup>–1</sup> from it ? 
<br>(Mass of electron = 9 $$ \times $$ 10<sup>–31</sup> kg;
<br>Velocity of light = 3 $$ \times $$ 10<sup>8</sup> ms<sup>$$-$$1</sup> 
<br>Plank's constant = 6.626 $$ \times $$ 10<sup>–34</sup> Js; 
<br>Charge of electron = 1.6 $$ \times $$10<sup>–19</sup> JeV<sup>–1</sup>)

